    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43052</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_001&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>&lt;Claus&gt;さんって料理はよく作ってくれっけど、
自分ではあんま食べないよな</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Mr. &lt;Claus&gt;, I noticed you always tend to prepare food
despite not really eating much food yourself.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>1</SpeakerId>
      <Id>1</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43124</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_002&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>ああ、少食な方だな</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Ahh, I get full easily.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>2</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43240</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_003&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>満腹になると頭が回らなくなる。
学者にとって食いすぎは致命的だ</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>To a member of the academe, filling oneself can be seen as fatal.
As a full stomach can dull one's own mind.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>3</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43320</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_004&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>腹三分目くらいでちょうどいい</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Eating enough to fill a third of my stomach is sufficient.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>4</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43408</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_005&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>そんなんで体とか大丈夫なんですか？</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Oh...Won't that be bad for your body, though?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>5</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43516</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_006&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>その分、別の栄養源をとってるから、
まったく問題ないぞ</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>In that respect, I derive my nutrients from a
completely different source.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>6</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43580</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_007&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>別の栄養源？</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Where?</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>7</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43720</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_008&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>ふくよかな甘い香り、口に入れれば熱き刺激、
すっと体内に落ちれば、たちまち心地よく……</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>A comforting drink that smells pleasantly rich, stimulating 
the tongue when placed within one's mouth.</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>8</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset>43832</PointerOffset>
      <VoiceId>&lt;audio:VCT_005_185_009&gt;</VoiceId>
      <JapaneseText>あっ……！　&lt;Claus&gt;、
またお酒飲んでるでしょ！　酒くさい！</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Agh! You've been drinking again, haven't you, &lt;Claus&gt;!?
You stink of alcohol, you old man!</EnglishText>
      <Notes/>
      <SpeakerId>4</SpeakerId>
      <Id>9</Id>
      <Status>Editing</Status>
    </Entry>
  </Strings>
